    think="Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me note important detai
ls about the mock infrastructure:\n\n1. `MockTweenManager.add()` immediately cal
ls `onComplete` synchronously! This means the current UIButton test where `emitE
vent(bg, 'pointerdown')` triggers onClick works because the mock tween immediate
ly completes.\n\n2. `MockScene.emit()` returns `this` (a MockContainer), not a b
oolean. The `MockContainer.emit()` returns `this`.\n\n3. For SceneSwitchBar, Pha
ser.Events.EventEmitter.emit() in real Phaser returns boolean, but our mock retu
rns `this`. The fix needs to be compatible with both.\n\nLet me now implement al
l the fixes. I'll do them in parallel where possible.\n\n**Fix 1: UIDialog.ts**\
nRemove `onOverlayClick` from `panelConfig` before `super()`, then after `super(
)` bind overlay click if `config.closeOnOverlay` is true.\n\n**Fix 2: UIButton.t
s**\nMove onClick from tween onComplete to pointerup. Add pointerupoutside. The 
test currently works because MockTweenManager calls onComplete synchronously, bu
t with the fix, we need to also call pointerup.\n\nWait, actually in the test:\n
```typescript\nemitEvent(bg, 'pointerdown');\nexpect(onClick).toHaveBeenCalled()
;\n```\n\nThis works because mock tween calls onComplete immediately. After our 
fix, we need:\n```typescript\nemitEvent(bg, 'pointerdown');\nemitEvent(bg, 'poin
terup');\nexpect(onClick).toHaveBeenCalled();\n```\n\n**Fix 3: SceneSwitchBar.ts
**\nThe issue is that `this.emit('before-switch', sceneType)` returns boolean (w
hether any listeners exist) not the result of listeners. We need to iterate list
eners and check their return values.\n\nIn the mock, `MockContainer.emit()` retu
rns `this`, which would be truthy. But in real Phaser it returns boolean.\n\nLoo
king at the code:\n```typescript\nconst canSwitch = this.emit('before-switch', s
ceneType);\n```\n\nWe need to replace this with something that checks actual lis
tener return values. Since Phaser's EventEmitter doesn't support this directly, 
we need to manually get listeners.\n\nActually, looking at Phaser's EventEmitter
, `listeners(event)` returns an array of listener functions. The fix in the revi
ew uses `this.listeners('before-switch')`. But our mock doesn't have `listeners(
)` method!\n\nLet me check if Phaser.EventEmitter has `listeners()`... The revie
w says:\n```typescript\nconst listeners = this.listeners('before-switch') as Arr
ay<(type: SceneType) => boolean>;\n```\n\nBut wait, `SceneSwitchBar` extends `Ph
aser.GameObjects.Container`, which extends `Phaser.Events.EventEmitter`. Phaser'
s EventEmitter does have `listeners()` method.\n\nOur mock `MockContainer` has `
events` property but no `listeners()` method. I need to add it to the mock, OR u
se a different approach.\n\nActually, I should check if tests will run and pass.
The tests for SceneSwitchBar may not exist. But I need to make the code work.\n\
nLet me look at what `listeners` does in Phaser. It returns the array of listene
rs for an event.\n\nFor our mock, we can add a `listeners` method to `MockContai
ner`:\n```typescript\nlisteners(event: string) {\n  return this.events[event] ??
[];\n}\n```\n\nBut wait, I'm modifying test-setup.ts which might affect other te
sts. Actually the fix is in SceneSwitchBar.ts, not in mock. Let me check if ther
e are existing tests for SceneSwitchBar.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at 
the review fix:\n```typescript\nconst listeners = this.listeners('before-switch'
) as Array<(type: SceneType) => boolean>;\nconst canSwitch = listeners.length ==
= 0 || listeners.every(fn => fn(sceneType));\n```\n\nThis should work if `this.l
